<br>
&quot;If I give you shelter, I must come with you.&quot; Omnia said to Anlore and floated into the air a foot. &quot;Something is coming.&quot; It turned around towards the forest. &quot;My home is in a nearby lake. You must be hasty, for I will not wait.&quot; With that the creature glided over the valley ground. At first the group is skeptical but they decide to follow. Caprice strayed behind the rest and asked herself, &quot;Did it say he lived in a lake?&quot;<br>
<br>
Omnia guided them around the forest edges and to a rather big crystal clear lake.  The creature floated to the edge of the water and turned to them, &quot;Can you people move that big boulder over there?&quot; It pointed to a big gray rock in the ground. &quot;That is the easiest way for people who have to breath. But if you want to swim.&quot; The creature moved it's six fingers lightly as it spoke. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/unitetimehero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nitetimehero</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/29/02 3:54:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=133>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.org/nitetimehero/cheese2.gif height=130 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shelter</span><hr size=1> &quot;I believe we can move the rock.&quot; said Elil.  &quot;Anlore, Cameron, Timothy, Van?&quot;<br>
