<br>
The rest of them were now walking in a long tunnel, water was up to their shins. Small candles lit the tunnel. They came to an opening and stepped in. A big table that could fit all of them was in the middle of the room. The ceiling reached very high. Chairs were spread out and a small fireplace was on the wall, unlit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/31/02 6:46:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=137>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why Not?</span><hr size=1> During the company's walk through the tunnels Caprice had unexpectantly slipped and fallen into the cold water.(She was a very clumsy person to begin with and the slippery floor of the tunnel had been of no help.)<br>
<br>
After arriving at the opening, Caprice had seated herself before the unlite fireplaces and began to search her pockets for flint and tinder. Finding none, she began to rub two sticks together in order to start a fire, grumbling as she did so.<br>
<br>
The other party members seated themselves at the table, looking about the room.<br>
&quot;I wonder if we can trust this Omnia,&quot;said Cameron.<br>
&quot;Who knows? It seems this company isn't exactly the best judge of character,&quot;replied Elil.<br>
&quot;That is true. Perhaps this character is diffrent. If he is all alone, it wouldn't be to unusual to ask for company,&quot;Timothy commented.<br>
Van gave a bit of a snort. &quot;But shelter in exchange for letting him join us? A bit radical,&quot;<br>
<br>
At that moment Caprice let out a frustrated yelled and flung the two sticks she had been holding to the size.<br>
&quot;I've had enough of this friction thing!&quot; She rubbed her palms together for a moment, then opened them up slightly, a little gap openening between her hands. She inhaled and placing her lips to the gap, blew out the air. Immediatly a small red light appeared from the space between her hands. Caprice opened her hands, a small flame dancing across them. She lowered the flame to the the wood and it instantly caught. she smiled happily and settled down in front of the fire, warming her hands.<br>
<br>
&quot;I thought you were an illusionist,&quot;commented Timothy.<br>
&quot;Well yeah,&quot;she replied. &quot;But before you cna do anything, you have to learn the basics. And making fire is one of them,&quot;<br>
<br>
The sound of light footsteps, only audiable to Elil became present.<br>
&quot;I think the other two have arrived,&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandxduke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrandxDuke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/1/02 12:07:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=138>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why Not?</span><hr size=1> In a poorly light room a slight haze of dust fills the air.  Strapped up against of a vertical table lays the broken body of Sonto.  A little shadow barely visible prances about behind the table, every now and then a shriek or cackle can be heard.<br>
<br>
Slowly the creature’s hand comes into view and takes Sonto’s left hand.  Revealing a small sharp object, something like a cross between a chisel and knife, Sonto finally wakes up.<br>
<br>
“What is it –“<br>
<br>
His words came out groggy but soon he would be fully alert as the object pierced his palm.<br>
<br>
With horror, “Don’t!  Don’t!  Stop, I’ve done nothing but follow Validus’s orders!”<br>
<br>
The chisel cuts down deep into his palm from bottom to top.  The voice came screechy, “You are strong, and smart.  But you are human, a weak one.  A little intelligence sacrificed for loyalty is worth it to the master.<br>
<br>
“Stop it!  I’ve followed his orders!  Don’t take my will away.  I’ll kill everyone of them!”<br>
<br>
For a second that scaring of Sonto’s hand is stopped, “You will?”<br>
<br>
“Yes!  Just let me keep my will.”<br>
<br>
“If I take it you will kill them anyways.”<br>
<br>
“No!”<br>
<br>
Sonto feebly struggles against his restraints as the imp like creature goes about tattooing his left palm.  It took nearly ten minutes for the insignia to be made and then staining powder to be added.  Sonto struggled and scream the whole time.<br>
<br>
Finally the imp spoke in Validus’s tongue and the insignia glowed bright.  With the insignia’s hew coming into this world Sonto’s mind left.  The insigne on his left hand began to pulsate and soon the right insignia joined in at the same pace.  Sonto’s eyes glazed over; his pupils almost appear to be loosing their color.<br>
<br>
“Much better, you won’t hesitate any longer to follow the Lord’s orders.”  The words came harsh slashing at the ears, though, Sonto’s mind no longer paid attention to the outside world.<br>
